{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 28 "Do the rest from 1 to 10.   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 31 "No
te:  it is possible to use a " }{TEXT 263 9 "for loop " }{TEXT -1 69 "
 to simplify this task since we are doing a repetitive calculation.  \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 29 "Note:  Also, the the command " }
{TEXT 265 6 "coeffs" }{TEXT -1 15 " unfortunately " }{TEXT 266 8 "does
 not" }{TEXT -1 36 " pick off the coefficients in order." }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 259 
16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for finding the c
oefficients of the expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"a
G\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 267 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is relatively obvious that the coefficient of  " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^(n-k)*b^k;" "6#*&)%\"aG,&%\"nG\"\"\"%\"kG!\"\"F()%\"b
GF)F(" }{TEXT -1 19 "  for any value of " }{TEXT 268 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 
11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 269 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by the numbe
r of ways we can choose " }{TEXT 270 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of the " }
{TEXT 294 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT 
-1 1 " " }{TEXT 295 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }
{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }
{TEXT -1 5 " ),  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The numbe
r of combinations of " }{TEXT 273 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosin
g " }{TEXT 274 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 " at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" 
"6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is given by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "
nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kG
F*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F*F2" }{TEXT -1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 261 10 "State the " }{TEXT 260 16 "Binomi
al Theorem" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 275 31 "and use Maple to demonstrat
e it" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 159 "If n is a positive integers, then \n\n(x + y)^n = C(n,
0)*x^n*y^0 + C(n,1)*x^(n-1)*y^1  + ... + C(n,r)*x^r*y^(n-r) + ... + C(
n,n-1)*x^1*y^(n-1) + C(n,n)*x^0*y^n. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 8 "Compute " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "sum(binomial
(n,k),k=0..n)" "6#-%$sumG6$-%)binomialG6$%\"nG%\"kG/F*;\"\"!F)" }
{TEXT -1 34 "  for n=1 to 10.  Here the symbol " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "Sigma
;" "6#%&SigmaG" }{TEXT -1 70 " (Greek letter Sigma) stands for sum.   \+
(See the worksheet SumSeq.mws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 46 "for n from 1 to 10\n do\n  e
xpand((a+b)^n);\n od;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"
%\"bGF%" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,(*$)%\"aG\"\"#\"\"\"F(*(F'
F(F&F(%\"bGF(F(*$)F*F'F(F(" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,**$)%\"
aG\"\"$\"\"\"F(*(F'F()F&\"\"#F(%\"bGF(F(*(F'F(F&F()F,F+F(F(*$)F,F'F(F(
