l formula do the above calculations in  suggest?" }}{PARA 258 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 43 "sum of the coefficients for each row = 2^n." }}{PARA 258 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 102 "For example row 4 has coefficients of 1,4,6,4,1.
 The sum of those coefficients is 16 which is = to 4^2" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 "2.  Pascal's Triang
le.  Recall the definition of Pascal's Triangle.   Use Maple to constr
uct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle. (The trick will be to get \+
the coefficients to occur in the correct order.  The Maple command for
 generating a sequence might be helpful. It is   seq(expression(i),i=m
..n);   where expression(i) is an expression with index i and m..n is \+
a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "   " }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 61 "for r from 0 to 10
\n do\n  seq(coeff((a+1)^r,a,i),i=0..r);\n od;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"\"F#" }}
