}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 214 "3.  Functions.  In this exeric
se we study the basic properties of polynomials and rational functions
.  Some revelant MAPLE commands will be   factor, expand, solve, fsolv
e, denom, numer, simplify, subs,   ....... ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 171 "     The first thing we need to learn is how to define a funct
ion.  There are two ways, each with its own advantages and disadvantag
es.  First define the polynomial p1 as " }{TEXT 282 2 "a " }{TEXT -1 
1 "s" }{TEXT 283 23 "ymbolic expression in x" }{TEXT -1 119 " in the f
ollowing way:    p1:=x^2-1;  (Note the colon before the =, this is alw
ays required when defining something.)  " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "p1:=x^2-1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p1G,
&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F*F*!\"\"" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 39 "     Now define the same polynomial as " 
}{TEXT 281 30 "an operation on the variable x" }{TEXT -1 40 " in the f
ollowing way:     p2:=x->x^2-1;" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "p2:=x->x^2-1;" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p2Gf*6#%\"xG6\"6$%)operatorG%&arrowGF(,&*$)9$
\"\"#\"\"\"F1F1!\"\"F(F(F(" }}}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 257 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 190 "Try the following command sequences to
 see some of the differences in how MAPLE  treats these two definition
s.  As always record your observations and comments on the worksheet i
n text mode." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "p1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"
\"#\"\"\"F(F(!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "p2;" }
}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%#p2G" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }{TEXT 299 98 "When defining expressions, function commands are nee
ded to execute and always refers to an object." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 300 92 "When using operations, arguments are need
ed such as  parenthesis and refers to an operation." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "p2(x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&
*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 8 "p2(t-3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
"" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$),&%\"tG\"\"\"\"\"$!\"\"\"\"#F(F(F(F*" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "p2(u^3-u^2+2);" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$),(*$)%\"uG\"\"$\"\"\"F+*$)F)\"\"#F+!\"\"F.F
+F.F+F+F+F/" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 255 "     This works just like we expect substitution to work
