\")%\"xG\"\"#F&!\"\"*&%\"bGF&F(F&F*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 61 "sets the equation equal to zero and solves for the variable c" 
}}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 2 "  " }
{TEXT 279 58 "What's the famous formula we get when we solve p3=0 for \+
x?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 301 21 "the Quadratic formu
la" }{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 169 "  See if MAPLE knows a general formula for solving gener
al cubic polynomials, i.e. is there a 3rd order formula comparable to \+
the quadratic formula?  If so, exhibit it. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "p4:=a*x^3+b*x^2+c*
x+d;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p4G,**&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"
\"$F(F(*&%\"bGF()F*\"\"#F(F(*&%\"cGF(F*F(F(%\"dGF(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "solve(p4=0,x);" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6%,(*(\"\"'!\"\"%\"aGF&,***\"#O\"\"\"%\"bGF+%\"cGF+F'F+F+
*(\"$3\"F+%\"dGF+)F'\"\"#F+F&*&\"\")F+)F,\"\"$F+F&**\"#7F+F6#F+F2,,*(
\"\"%F+F'F+)F-F6F+F+*&)F-F2F+)F,F2F+F&*,\"#=F+F,F+F-F+F'F+F0F+F&*(\"#F
F+)F0F2F+F1F+F+*(F<F+F0F+F5F+F+F9F'F+F+#F+F6F+*,F2F+F6F&,&*(F6F+F'F+F-
F+F+*$F@F+F&F+F'F&F(#F&F6F&*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&,**(F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F&FIF
+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&*(^#F9F+F6F9,&*(F%F&F'F&F(FGF+*,F2F+F6F&FIF
+F'F&F(FLF+F+F+,**(F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&*
(^##F&F2F+F6F9FTF+F+" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 280 111 "Why do you think high school stude
nts are never asked to remember the general formula for the roots of a
 cubic?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 302 49 "because that w
ould be crazy, students would rebel" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 113 "4.  Solving Equations in One Variable. \+
  There are two different commands to direct Maple to solve an equatio
n:  " }{TEXT 285 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 286 7 "fsolve." 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "They have different purposes.  The " }
{TEXT 287 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 63 " command attempts to find exact solu
tions.  If the expression  " }{TEXT 289 1 "f" }{TEXT -1 116 "  is defi
ned in terms of only one variable, there are several different ways to
 direct Maple to solve the equation  " }{TEXT 290 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 
291 4 "0.  " }{TEXT -1 54 "The following all cause Maple to solve the \+
equation   " }{TEXT 292 5 "f  = " }{TEXT 293 2 "0." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 16 "       solve(f);" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f,x);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 18 "       solve(f=0);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 20 "      \+
 solve(f=0,x);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 349 "Maple makes an assumption that if the coefficients of a \+
polynomial are all given exactly (as integers or rational numbers [rat
ios of integer]), then you are only interested in finding exact soluti
ons.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra doesn't guarantee that the so
lutions of  a polynomial can be found exactly, only the polynomial has
 solutions.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 78 "You can force Maple to report additional (approximate) so
lutions by using the " }{TEXT 288 6 "fsolve" }{TEXT -1 11 " command.  \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 31 "(What does the \"f\" stand for?  " }
{TEXT 303 30 "It stands for floating points." }{TEXT -1 1 ")" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 252 "In addition, to forcing Maple to report approx
imate solutions, you can specify a field extension (typically real or \+
complex) and require Maple to look for solutions which fit in that fie
ld extension.  Also, one can specify a range of x values and force" }
{TEXT 296 7 " fsolve" }{TEXT -1 75 " to only look for solutions in tha
t specified range.  For example, compare:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "fsolve(4*x-x^3);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6%$!+++++?!\"*$\"\"!F'$\"+++++?F%" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "fsolve(4*x-x^3,x=1..4);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+++++?!\"*" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 176 "in the first comm
and you set the expression equal to zero and solved for all roots, the
 second command you set the expression and said that x can only be val
ues between 1 ... 4" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 28 "For each of the polynom
ials " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p[1]" "6#&%\"pG6#\"\"\"" }{TEXT -1 9 " through \+
" }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p[14]" "6#&%\"pG6#\"#9" }{TEXT -1 19 ", do the follo
wing:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 56 "     a.   solve for all exact ro
ots whereever possible, " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 59 "     b.   fin
d all approximate roots to 10 decimal places, " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 43 "     c.  factor each into linear factors.  " }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 106 "You will need to \+
click on  [> in the toolbar to obtain new execution lines just below t
he cursor position." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "p1:= x^2-2;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#>%#p1G,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F*F)!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "solve(p1);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$*$\"\"##\"\"\"F$,$F#!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG 
